public abstract class AbstractDeserializer<OUTPUT>
extends Object
implements Deserializer<OUTPUT>

An abstract implementation of Deserializer which directs deserialization for all Deserializers. To create a custom Deserializer extend this class and override deserialize(InvocationContext, HttpResponse).

Note that all implementations are expected to be stateless. If a state is incurred, proper ThreadLocal management should be performed.

deserialize

protected abstract OUTPUT deserialize(InvocationContext context,
                                      org.apache.http.HttpResponse response)

Takes an HttpResponse which resulted from a successful request execution and deserializes its content to an instance of the output type.

The response HttpEntity can be obtained using HttpResponse.getEntity() and its content can be stringified with EntityUtils.toString(HttpEntity).

Note that certain HttpResponses may not contain an HttpEntity which can be confirmed by performing a null check on HttpResponse.getEntity().

Note that any runtime errors which might occur during serialization are caught, wrapped in an instance of DeserializerException (stack-trace preserved) and allowed to bubble up.

Parameters:
response - the HttpResponse of a successful request execution

context - the InvocationContext which supplies all information regarding the request and it's invocation

Returns:
the content which resulted from deserializing the response entity

Since:
1.1.4
